This paper is likely to belong to the category of machine learning (cs.LG) as it proposes a new variant of importance sampling that can reduce the variance of importance sampling-based estimates. It also discusses how this new estimator can be used to improve estimates of how well a new treatment policy for diabetes will work for an individual, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also provides a detailed theoretical analysis, which involves statistical inference and probability theory, making it relevant to the categories of statistics (cs.ST) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the example of using the new estimator for treatment policy evaluation suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the category of control systems (cs.SY).
